quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  42,1,"Ha Mīm."
  42,2,"’Ayn Sîn Qaf."
  42,3,"Thus <span class=""h"">reveals<sup foot_note=""81075"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">—to you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=""h"">and to those before you—Allah the Almighty, the All-Wise.</span>"
  42,4,"<span class=""h"">To</span>Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and He is the All-High, the Great."
  42,5,"The heavens almost <span class=""h"">splinter<sup foot_note=""81076"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>from above them, while the angels exalt their Lord with praise and ask forgiveness for those on earth. Undoubtedly, Allah is indeed the Oft-Forgiving, the Bestower of mercy."
  42,6,"And those who take guardians apart from Him—Allah is a Constant Preserver over them, for you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are not a trustee over them."
  42,7,"And thus We revealed to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>an Arabic Recital{1}, that you may warn the Mother of Towns{2}and those around it and warn of the Day of Assembly, of which there is no doubt: a group in the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>and a group in the Blaze.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.|2:Makkah.
  42,8,"And had Allah willed, He could have made them one community, but He enters into His mercy whomever He wills, while the unjust have neither ally nor supporter."
  42,9,"Or have they taken others as guardians apart from Him? Yet Allah is the Ultimate Guardian, and He gives life to the dead, and He is All-Powerful over everything."
  42,10,"And whatever matter you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>differ over— its judgment rests with Allah. “Such is Allah, my Lord; in Him I have placed my trust and to Him I turn penitently.”"
